RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR ILLINOIS REGISTERED, CONCEIVED AND/OR FOALED. Maidens, Fillies And Mares Three Years Old and Upward. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SLEEPY CAT broke outwardly then moved forward outside rivals up the backstretch, drew even outside the leader three deep about the five-sixteenths, was in command at the top of the stretch, edged clear then held sway under steady but moderate urging. MISS MIA tracked from inside, moved out a bit early on the turn, continued to shift out fanning six wide into upper stretch, ran on to secure the place. TENSE broke a step slowly while brushing the gate then steadied when in tight leaving the stalls, switched out racing off the inside up the backstretch, began to advance some leaving the turn in the four path before moving back in a bit, advanced between runners in mid-stretch and ran on. JEMEZ FALLS shifted in tracking the leaders inside, saved ground on the turn, angled five wide turning for home and ran on evenly. LUTION raced near the inside off the leaders, passed a rival two wide running on evenly. MISS HIGH N MIGHTY was urged forward to set the pace racing on or just off the rail, gave way in the stretch. TIS SYRIAN KITTY was outpaced, distanced, walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Tis Syrian Kitty
ENTRY.COMMENT: outpaced, distanced, walked off

ENTRY.NAME: Tense
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, brushed gate & stdy'd start, off inside, 2-4p, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Mia
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, fanned 6w, secured place

ENTRY.NAME: Lution
ENTRY.COMMENT: near inside, 2wide, evenly, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Miss High N Mighty
ENTRY.COMMENT: urged forward, pace, inside-2path, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Jemez Falls
ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in, tracked inside, angled 5wd 1/4, evenly, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Sleepy Cat
ENTRY.OWNER: Robertson Hugh H Mentz John and Fisher Ray D
ENTRY.COMMENT: brk out, forwardly outside, 3w, even 5/16, command 1/4, clr, held

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Hugh Robertson, John Mentz & Ray Fisher

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 9 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race at a mile or over since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HER GOLD MINE moved clear but six wide entering the first turn, shifted in on the early part of that bend to set the pace racing in about the two path and in the clear, responded when asked and drew off. KITTEN ROCKS was caught five then four wide on the first turn moving up outside rivals, stalked the pacesetter and eventual winner, edged a bit closer three to four wide on the far turn looming a threat coming near the top of the stretch, drifted out in upper stretch, was headed for second but fought back to regain the place while no threat to the winner. TWELVE RED ROSES was brushed at the break, caught four wide into the first turn then taken back and shifted in saving ground the remainder of that bend in behind the second group, tipped out up the backstretch, advanced three to four wide on the far turn looming a threat turning for home, was carried out six deep in upper stretch by a drifting rival, put a head in front of that one into second place but was outfinished and settled for show honors. WEEKEND PASS was unhurried early, swung six wide into upper stretch ran on. QUEEN EKATI raced between foes tracking the leader two wide into the first turn, dropped back and tipped out for the run up the backstretch, began a rapid move about the five-sixteenths four wide, swung six wide into upper stretch then altered inside drifting rivals about the three-sixteenths, ran on evenly. AH LEAH tracked from inside, saved ground, steadily dropped back and failed to rally. ZANDREA'S brushed a rival lightly at the start, stalked three wide between runners on the first turn, steadily dropped back two to three wide on the far turn, tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Ah Leah
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Queen Ekati
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2wd early, dropped back & moved out, 4wd move 5/16, alter in 3/16

ENTRY.NAME: Weekend Pass
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, swung 6wide, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Zandrea's
ENTRY.COMMENT: brush foe brk, stalked 3wd btw early, dropped back 2-3w, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Twelve Red Roses
ENTRY.COMMENT: brush brk, shift in early, 3-4w 2nd, carried out, outfnshd place

ENTRY.NAME: Kitten Rocks
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5-4w 1st turn, loom 3-4w 2nd, drift out upper, fought for place

ENTRY.NAME: Her Gold Mine
ENTRY.COMMENT: moved clear, shifted in 1st turn, pace, responded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 9. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCESS STELLA (IRE) got away alertly, set the pace in the clear racing near the inside, drew off when asked under steady hand urging. FOGGY KITTEN switched outside the early leader, stalked that one going two wide into the turn, was no match but held the place. SILVERA settled inside a foe off the pace racing off the inside, moved in a bit going three wide on the turn, asked for more about the five-sixteenths, swung six deep into upper stretch, kept on late to narrowly miss second. AUNT STELLA was a bit fractious in the gate, broke outwardly, gained forward position tracking from inside, angled four wide turning for home, made no late bid. ARCH FLYER was a step slow and in tight then steadied just slightly at the start, brought up the rear, swung off the inside turning for home and passed tired rivals. IRISH HALO shifted in early, saved ground, failed to rally. PRINCESS CONSUELA was caught outside a rival early going four wide into the turn, fanned seven deep for the drive and failed to rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Aunt Stella
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, brk out, tracked inside, angled 4w, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Arch Flyer
ENTRY.COMMENT: tight brk & stdy'd, off inside, passed foes

ENTRY.NAME: Foggy Kitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out early, stalked winner, 2w, no match, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Stella (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, clear, pace, drew off, hand urging

ENTRY.NAME: Silvera
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 3wd turn, swung 6wd, kept on, missed 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in, saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Consuela
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside, 4-7w, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 9. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIME HEIST pressed from inside then engaged the leader more thoroughly to duel inside, took command just past the three-sixteenths and forged clear under urging. RESTORING HOPE broke a half-step slowly, switched outside rivals and moved up four wide on the turn, kept on in the lane to get up for second. ACT OF BOB broke outwardly quite a bit then moved forward and clear to force the pace from outside, was engaged by an inside foe up the backstretch, dueled with that one, yielded in upper- to mid-stretch and lost place late. EASTER MUSIC switched off the rail early, raced toward the back, angled six wide turning for home, drifted out a bit, ran on. DEVIL'S RULE broke inwardly, moved out off the inside to race about three wide early on the turn, fanned seven wide put to strong urging and beginning to pick it up, was carried out a bit in upper stretch before shifting in, ran on evenly thereafter. WILLOW RIDGE tracked from the two path inside rivals mid-pack, failed to rally. SPEEDY G chased from between runners three wide into the turn, dropped back and moved out five wide coming out of that bend, failed to rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Devil's Rule
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke inwardly, off inside, fanned 7w, shifted in mid-str

ENTRY.NAME: Easter Music
ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out early, angled 6wd into str, drifted bit, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Willow Ridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 2path mid-pack, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Restoring Hope
ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow, switched out, 4wd turn, up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Speedy G
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3wd btw into turn, came out 5wd, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Time Heist
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, dueled, command 3/16, forged clear

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outwardly, forced pace outside, dueled, yielded, lost place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners of a race at a mile or over since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Claiming races for $40,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances) (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACT A FOOL was lightly bumped and stumbled at the start, recovered to move forward and clear dictating the pace on or just off the rail, shook off rivals, kicked clear and was kept to the task. WESLAN shifted in early on the first turn, tracked the leaders inside advancing quickly to take closer order up the backstretch, lost ground dropping back on the far turn but kept on in the stretch to gain the place over GEM COLLECTION, who was encouraged forward to stalk the eventual winner two to three wide, was floated a bit wider by the leader into the stretch, could not kick on with that one and lost place. SIVAKO broke a bit awkwardly, was forced out four wide into the first turn, moved in up the backstretch racing mid-pack two to three wide through the far turn, ran on in the lane but needed more. MONGOLIAN BEE broke inwardly bumping a rival with a bit of force, lacked early speed bringing up the rear, angled out in upper stretch and ran on with mild interest. EL RAYO stalked just off the pace three to four wide, came up empty. FAITHFUL KING was bumped hard and squeezed back at the start, rank early fighting the rider and drifting out on the first turn, tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Act a Fool
ENTRY.OWNER: Patricia's Hope LLC and Ravin Richard
ENTRY.COMMENT: bmp, stumbled start, pace, insd-2p, clear, kept task

ENTRY.NAME: Faithful King

ENTRY.NAME: Mongolian Bee
ENTRY.COMMENT: brk in, bump foe, no speed, angled out upper

ENTRY.NAME: Sivako
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit awkward brk, forced 4wd 1st turn, 2-3w 2nd, ran on

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked winner 2-3w, floated 4w, no late kick, lost place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,500 (Claiming races for $6,250 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINGING WAYS was urged clear to dictate terms, set the pace inside, drew clear in the stretch and was kept to the task. CHICKS FOR FREE was bumped at the start, raced at the back, began to advance outside foes four then five wide on the turn, altered inside a drifting rival for room near the sixteenth pole and captured the place. PUBLIC SAFETY raced just off the leaders mid-pack going three to four wide on the turn, came out further for the drive and ran on. CHRISTMAS PRESENT saved ground and ran on evenly. SOUPER FORTUNE was forced out at the start then coaxed forward, chased the leaders racing just off the rail in about the two to three path, had no extra. JACK VAN BERG was urged at the break but outsprinted early, chased the eventual winner just off that one, could not kick on and drifted out in mid- to late-stretch while weakening. KING TITO broke outwardly bothering a rival, switched out racing at the back off the inside, fanned eight wide into upper stretch, was never a threat. RENEGADE BOB bumped a rival at the start, dropped back two to three wide and failed to rally. C C'S KITTEN was bumped into a rival at the start, chased from between foes three wide into the turn then moved in a bit, faded in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Claiming races for $25,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances) (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHARP HERO pressed the pace just off the leader, bid outside the five-sixteenths, was in command by the quarter pole, forged clear in upper stretch and held sway. STOPSHOPPINGAMY was brushed lightly at the start, outsprinted early, raced near the rail through the turn, rallied between runners in mid- to late-stretch for the place. RACETOTHEFINISH bobbled outwardly just slightly at the start brushing a rival, pursued the pace from outside four wide, needed more. WAY TOO SMARTE was outpaced early racing outside well back of the leaders through the turn, raced three to six wide throughout and improved position. DOCS SEVEN attended the early pace three wide and between, weakened. INDICIA was outpaced and not a factor. JUST A WONDER set the pace inside facing some outside pressure, gave way in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 8 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MODIFIER broke a half-step slowly, moved forward under some coaxing going three to four wide on the first turn stalking the pace, edged closer leaving the backstretch, launched a bid three wide and took charge outside the five-sixteenths, drew clear by mid-stretch and was eased up late. GOLD SMOKE switched off the inside early racing in the three to four path at the back into the first turn, advanced heading to the far turn, moved out from three to five wide on that bend, ran on to be second best while no threat to the winner. KITTEN'S CLOWN raced off the pace two to three wide early, continued well back of the leaders two deep on the far turn, kept on in the drive to get show honors. HIGHLY UNLIKELY was forced out four to five wide by a rival at the rear entering the first turn, settled up the backstretch racing two to three wide into the far turn, came out a bit in upper stretch then lugged in, ran on to improve position. WICKED SUPRISE pursued the pace two to three wide, lacked the needed late kick. SUMMER COUNTRY was caught four to five wide through the first turn, raced well-positioned up the backstretch into the far turn off the leaders three wide, failed to rally. FITZEA saved ground on the first turn, switched out racing well off the inside up the backstretch, was never a factor. LIMA ZULU brushed the gate lightly, was urged clear to set the pace inside, wilted.

ENTRY.OWNER: Bentler Judy and Martin William R
ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out, 3-4path, 3-5w 2nd turn, second best
